  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7101 sitting just above the max negative gamma strike at 7100, dealers are likely buying dips here as they're short gamma at this level, providing immediate support. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls at 7150 (+5649M) and 7200 (+7369M) creates a strong gravitational pull higher, where dealers will increasingly sell rallies as spot approaches these levels. Watch 7100 as the key inflection point - a break below could trigger dealer selling into negative gamma territory down to the flip at 6872, while any move toward 7150-7200 should face increasing dealer resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect upward drift toward 7150-7200 with strong support at 7100.",
